verses.text:
\add And\add* nets of checker work, and wreaths of chain work,
for the chapiters which \add were\add* upon the top of the pillars;
seven for the one chapiter, and seven for the other chapiter.

(For they shall hear of thy great name, and of thy strong hand,
and of thy stretched out arm;) when he shall come and pray toward this
house;

For it came to pass, when David was in Edom, and Joab the
captain of the host was gone up to bury the slain, after he had smitten
every male in Edom;

Him that dieth of Jeroboam in the city shall the dogs eat;
and him that dieth in the field shall the fowls of the air eat: for the
\nd LORD\nd* hath spoken \add it\add*.

¶ And Jeroboam’s wife arose, and departed, and came to Tirzah:
\add and\add* when she came to the threshold of the door, the child
died;

¶ Then were the people of Israel divided into two parts: half
of the people followed Tibni the son of Ginath, to make him king;
and half followed Omri.

And the messengers came again, and said, Thus speaketh Ben-hadad,
saying, Although I have sent unto thee, saying, Thou shalt deliver
me thy silver, and thy gold, and thy wives, and thy children;

And \add one\add* washed the chariot in the pool of Samaria;
and the dogs licked up his blood; and they washed his armour; according unto the
word of the \nd LORD\nd* which he spake.
